-- Peru Stocks: Candente, Ferreyros, Panoro, Rio Alto, Siderperu
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-01-12T21:24:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/peru-stocks-candente-ferreyros-panoro-rio-alto-siderperu.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for a fourth session, gaining
1.3 percent to 20,539.69. The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  climbed
0.9 percent to 2,645.85.  Industrial shares gained after U.S. stocks advanced, said
Estefany Castillo, an analyst at Scotiabank Peru.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POM\C)  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar
producer, rose 4.1 percent to 51 centimos.  Empresa Siderurgica
del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau SA known as
Siderperu, climbed 3.5 percent to 89 centimos.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1) 
(FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for Caterpillar Inc.,
gained 2.6 percent to 2.39 soles.  Copper and gold miners rose after metals gained in New York
and  London .  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian gold and copper
exploration company, advanced 9.3 percent to 47 cents.  Rio Alto
Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian company with a mine in Peru,
climbed 3.6 percent to $3.73.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a
Canadian exploration company, rose 4.3 percent to 98 cents.
 Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peruâ€™s biggest copper producer,
